    <div class="section">
      

<div id="review_1269934513" class="review nosyndicate" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/1269934513" />
    <a title="Stephie Williams" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/28825839-stephie-williams"><img alt="Stephie Williams" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1618529948p2/28825839.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/1269934513?book_show_action=true">May 02, 2015</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Stephie Williams" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Stephie Williams" href="/user/show/28825839-stephie-williams">Stephie Williams</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer1269934513" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer2801040382337269517">I felt it was a real good book on the history of freethought and secularism in American history. Although, working from mostly secondary sources, Jacoby presents a readable volume on how the enlightment of rational thinking has influenced poltics in America. She kept the narative going with understandable prose, good characteristics for any writer, but especially for one who is writing about more complex subject matter. Her conclusion for modern day freethinkers is not encouraging. It seems like</span>
  <span id="freeText2801040382337269517" style="display:none">I felt it was a real good book on the history of freethought and secularism in American history. Although, working from mostly secondary sources, Jacoby presents a readable volume on how the enlightment of rational thinking has influenced poltics in America. She kept the narative going with understandable prose, good characteristics for any writer, but especially for one who is writing about more complex subject matter. Her conclusion for modern day freethinkers is not encouraging. It seems like a large task to overcome the influence and damage done by the religious right. For a freethinker remember who your voting for.</span>
  <a data-text-id="2801040382337269517" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


      <div class="reviewFooter uitext buttons">
          

