<div id="review_820604458" class="review nosyndicate" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/820604458" />
    <a title="Brad" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/253799-brad"><img alt="Brad" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1579492697p2/253799.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/820604458?book_show_action=true">Jan 11, 2014</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Brad" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Brad" href="/user/show/253799-brad">Brad</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Hardcover 9780805074420" href="/book/show/1635636.Freethinkers">review of another edition</a>


        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/253799-brad?shelf=favorites">favorites</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/253799-brad?shelf=non-fiction">non-fiction</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer820604458" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer7023509663367439962">I took this book as the rallying cry it was meant to be. If you read it and emerge from it apathetic, then you are truly lost. &quot;Secularists&quot;, atheists, and their ilk should understand that they should not be interested only in themselves or their own causes, but in the causes of all of humanity, religious and nonreligious. Assaults on science and secularism threaten to undermine not just the civil liberties and the average intelligence of Americans, but the entire moral code of the nation. How c</span>
  <span id="freeText7023509663367439962" style="display:none">I took this book as the rallying cry it was meant to be. If you read it and emerge from it apathetic, then you are truly lost. "Secularists", atheists, and their ilk should understand that they should not be interested only in themselves or their own causes, but in the causes of all of humanity, religious and nonreligious. Assaults on science and secularism threaten to undermine not just the civil liberties and the average intelligence of Americans, but the entire moral code of the nation. How can the encouragement of legalized murder even, for just a second, be suggested as a wholesome form of morality? No man, under any circumstance, regardless of belief, wants to die--how can we impose death on others?<br /><br />A freethinker should hold him or herself to one standard: we shall not endeavor to inflict upon others what we would not want for ourselves. As such it is our duty, our moral imperative, to stand up for all people, regardless of gender, sexuality, or religion, and say that we will not stand for any injustice visited upon them. We can no longer reside in muted apathy, for we would not want others to look at our own status with such apathy when it is our time in bondage.</span>
  <a data-text-id="7023509663367439962" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


